<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-SQql0KGbTgagsQfN8_4dWw" name=",_89A28KZtEeCmPtYkD7g0pw" guid="-SQql0KGbTgagsQfN8_4dWw" changeDate="2011-08-24T06:40:55.850-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The execution of the validation plan provides&amp;nbsp;a rationale regarding the absence of faulty activation of safety&#xD;
    mechanisms due to operational situations, system or feature interactions or use cases. If testing is used for&#xD;
    validation then the same requirements for testing as provided for verification apply.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The characteristics of controllability, the effectiveness of the safety measures for controlling random and systematic&#xD;
    failures, the external measures and the elements of other technology involved in the integrated item , shall be&#xD;
    validated at the vehicle level against the safety goals, functional safety requirements and the intended use. The&#xD;
    validation details shall also include the scope of the application, i.e. configuration, environmental conditions, use&#xD;
    cases, driving situation, and &amp;nbsp;the validation test procedures and test cases for each safety goal including&#xD;
    detailed pass fail criteria.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The validation of random hardware failures shall be carried out at the item level in accordance with the architectural&#xD;
    metrics and in accordance with the assessment criteria detailed in ISO 26262, volume 5, clause 9. This is recommended for&#xD;
    items with an ASIL of B and highly recommended for items with an ASIL of C or D.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Methods that can be applied for validation are the following:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Reproducible tests with specified test procedures, test cases and pass/fail criteria.&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Analysis, (Simulation, FMEA, FTA, ETA)&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Long term tests (such as vehicle driving schedules and data captured from test fleets)&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        User test under real life conditions, panel or blind tests, expert panels and reviews.&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The results of the validation will be evaluated and presented as a report.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></mainDescription>
  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    To ensure that it is not possible to activate the safety mechanisms inappropriately at the vehicle level.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
